PN,39301
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FA man who violently beat and raped a
OL,8,Fwoman in 2003 - in an attack that led
OL,9,Fto the wrongful conviction of another
OL,10,Fman who spent 17 years in prison - has
OL,11,Fbeen given an extended sentence of 24
OL,12,Fyears.
OL,14,FPaul Quinn, 52, evaded justice for
OL,15,Fmore than two decades but was found
OL,16,Fguilty of two counts of rape, one
OL,17,Fcount of choking with intent and one
OL,18,Fcount of grievous bodily harm after
OL,19,Fnew DNA technology linked him to the
OL,20,Fcrime.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FThe victim, a then-mother-of-two who
OL,8,Fcannot be named for legal reasons, was
OL,9,Fwalking along Cleggs Lane in Little
OL,10,FHulton, near Salford, in the early
OL,11,Fhours of 19 July 2003 when she was
OL,12,Fpushed down an embankment before being
OL,13,Fwas beaten, raped and strangled by
OL,14,FQuinn.
OL,16,FDuring the trial, the victim gave
OL,17,Fevidence and told the court her last
OL,18,Fmemory before being strangled
OL,19,Funconscious was a man on top of her
OL,20,Fwith his hands around her neck.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FAfter an e-fit based on a description
OL,8,Fof the attacker was produced by
OL,9,Fpolice, Andrew Malkinson was picked
OL,10,Fout of a digital identity parade by
OL,11,Fthe victim and two other witnesses -
OL,12,Fdespite no DNA evidence linking him to
OL,13,Fthe crime.
OL,15,FMr Malkinson served 17 years behind
OL,16,Fbars for a crime he did not commit.
OL,17,FNow aged 60, he was only released in
OL,18,F2020 after 17 years in jail, with his
OL,19,Fconviction finally quashed by the
OL,20,FCourt of Appeal in 2023.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FQuinn always denied any involvement in
OL,8,Fthe brutal attack and was never linked
OL,9,Fto the crime until 2022 when new
OL,10,Fevidence emerged.
OL,12,FHe was convicted after a six-week
OL,13,Ftrial at Manchester Crown Court.
OL,15,FDuring sentencing Mr Justice Bright,
OL,16,Fdescribed Quinn's victim as a "hero",
OL,17,Fpaying credit to her "quiet dignity"
OL,18,Fat having to give evidence in two
OL,19,Ftrials.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FHe added: "She is a remarkable person,
OL,8,Fand I say all this to give public
OL,9,Ftribute her, and to others like her.
OL,11,F"They do not come here for vengeance,
OL,12,Fwhich we do not give them, they do not
OL,13,Fcome expecting closure, which is a
OL,14,Flargely mythical phenomenon,
OL,15,Fespecially after an event such as
OL,16,Frape, they come because they want the
OL,17,Ftruth to be heard and because they
OL,18,Fknow it is the right thing to do.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"Without them it would not be possible
OL,8,Fto bring the guilty ones to justice -
OL,9,Fand this is why she, far above any of
OL,10,Fthe police, or the lawyers or the DNA
OL,11,Fscientists is the hero of this story."
OL,13,FIn a victim impact statement, the
OL,14,Fmother told the court "for him it was
OL,15,Fone night of his life, for me it was
OL,16,Fone night that changed my life."
OL,18,FShe said: "After 20 years, I now have
OL,19,Fjustice but that does not change the
OL,20,Ffact that two lives have been impacted
OL,21,Fin such a way.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"I am aware that someone has had 17
OL,8,Fyears robbed as a result of this case
OL,9,Fand that stays with me.
OL,11,F"As for me, the impact of what
OL,12,Fhappened that day has stayed with me
OL,13,Fand will remain with me for life."
OL,15,FTurning his attention to Quinn, who
OL,16,Fmade no reaction, Mr Justice Bright,
OL,17,Fsaid he had "seen no sign he has ever
OL,18,Frepented" for what he had done, adding
OL,19,Fhe had instead "sat back and enjoyed
OL,20,Fyour liberty at the expense of another
OL,21,Fman".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"Your stance remains that you deny
OL,8,Fcommitting the offences, that is by
OL,9,Fdefinition not a stance I accept, but
OL,10,Fit means as you appear before me today
OL,11,Fyou appear apparently without remorse
OL,12,Fand without regret and you appear to
OL,13,Fhave no readiness to tackle the
OL,14,Fcauses, characteristics and
OL,15,Fcircumstances that led to the
OL,16,Foffending," he said.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FSentencing him to 21 years in jail,
OL,8,Fwith an extra three years on licence
OL,9,Fafter release, Mr Justice Bright also
OL,10,Faddressed Quinn on Mr Malkinson's
OL,11,Fwrongful conviction.
OL,13,F"It is utterly clear that you knew
OL,14,Fthroughout that another man had been
OL,15,Farrested, charged, convicted and
OL,16,Fimprisoned," he told him.
OL,26,@uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"You knew that his conviction was
OL,8,Fwrongful. You also knew that it was
OL,9,Fextremely useful to you. It must have
OL,10,Fplayed on your conscience that another
OL,11,Fman was in prison, in effect, serving
OL,12,Fyour sentence.
OL,14,F"It certainly should have played on
OL,15,Fyour conscience that you were only too
OL,16,Fwilling to sit back and take advantage
OL,17,Fof his misfortune.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"It is true that you never did
OL,8,Fanything positive to implicate Mr
OL,9,FMalkinson, however but for your
OL,10,Foffending he never would have been
OL,11,Fquestioned."
OL,13,FThe court heard Quinn, aged 29 at the
OL,14,Ftime of the attack and who lived
OL,15,Flocally before moving to Exeter,
OL,16,FDevon, was only linked to the crime
OL,17,Fafter scientific advances matched his
OL,18,FDNA profile from samples left on the
OL,19,Fvictim.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G11/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39312
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FThe DNA findings estimate it would be
OL,8,Fat least one billion times more likely
OL,9,Fif Quinn was a contributor to the
OL,10,Fsample found at the crime scene than
OL,11,Fif he was not.
OL,13,FIt was also told five years before Mr
OL,14,FMalkinson's conviction was overturned
OL,15,FQuinn had been researching it online,
OL,16,Fvisiting an article in 2019, about his
OL,17,Fconviction before, moments later,
OL,18,Fsearching "wrongful convictions uk".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G12/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39313
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FIn court, Quinn claimed his internet
OL,8,Fsearches were a "complete
OL,9,Fcoincidence", but officers from
OL,10,FGreater Manchester Police said at the
OL,11,Ftime of the Google search, no-one
OL,12,Fapart from Mr Malkinson and his legal
OL,13,Fteam knew his case was a wrongful
OL,14,Fconviction.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G13/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39314
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FShortly after news of a DNA
OL,8,Fbreakthrough in the case, Quinn also
OL,9,Fbegan researching 'how long DNA is
OL,10,Fkept on police databases', whether
OL,11,Fsamples could be removed, and queried
OL,12,F"why do I keep sweating all the time?"
OL,13,Fand "why am I sweating so much all of
OL,14,Fa sudden?"
OL,16,FQuinn was only told, for the first
OL,17,Ftime, his DNA had ben found on the
OL,18,Fvictim's clothing when arrested on 13
OL,19,FDecember 2022.
OL,26,@tD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G14/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39315
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FFallout from the case includes a
OL,8,Fpublic inquiry which is now under way
OL,9,Fafter a 2024 review found failings
OL,10,Fthat could have exonerated Mr
OL,11,FMalkinson a decade before he was
OL,12,Feventually released from prison.
OL,14,FFive former Greater Manchester Police
OL,15,Fofficers and one currently serving
OL,16,Fwith the force are under investigation
OL,17,Fby the Independent Office for Police
OL,18,FConduct (IOPC) with both the chair and
OL,19,Fchief executive of the Criminal Cases
OL,20,FReview Commission (CCRC) having
OL,21,Fresigned.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G15/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39316
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,FThe trial heard Mr Malkinson was the
OL,8,Fvictim of one of the worst examples of
OL,9,Fa miscarriage of justice in British
OL,10,Fcriminal history.
OL,12,FFollowing the sentencing, Mr Malkinson
OL,13,Fsaid he hoped Quinn, who had "let me
OL,14,Frot" in prison, did not get parole
OL,15,Fwhich would see him serve around 14
OL,16,Fyears of his 21 year custodial
OL,17,Fsentence.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G16/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39317
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"I am insulted that this violent,
OL,8,Fdepraved individual - who was content
OL,9,Fto let me suffer two decades of
OL,10,Fvilification and more than 17 years
OL,11,Fwrongly imprisoned for his crime - has
OL,12,Freceived a softer sentence than was
OL,13,Fimposed on me, an innocent man," he
OL,14,Fsaid.
OL,16,F"I got sentenced to life imprisonment
OL,17,Fand served more than 17 years inside.
OL,18,FThroughout that time I didn't know if
OL,19,FI would ever be released.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G17/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39318
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"Paul Quinn, who has a track record of
OL,8,Fviolence and sexual offences, and who
OL,9,Flet me rot whilst he enjoyed his
OL,10,Ffreedom, could now be out after just
OL,11,F14 years, and will certainly be out
OL,12,Fafter 21 years.
OL,14,F"I hope that this man does not get
OL,15,Fparole and that he serves longer than
OL,16,Fme. Anything less is not justice.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G18/19
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39319
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1780751473
OL,3,CSex offender sentenced to 24 years
OL,4,Cafter wrongful conviction of Andrew
OL,5,CMalkinson
OL,7,F"I am also appalled for the victim,
OL,8,Fwho has suffered so gravely and whose
OL,9,Freal attacker has today gotten off
OL,10,Flightly. My thoughts are with her and
OL,11,Fher loved ones - who I hope today
OL,12,Fnevertheless brings some peace."
OL,14,FWant more on the issues effecting the
OL,15,FNorth? Our podcast, From the North
OL,16,Fanswers the questions that matter to
OL,17,Four region.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
